OL,3,CShould the Channel Islands compel
OL,4,Ccriminals to face victims in court?
OL,6,FThere are growing calls for defendants
OL,7,Fto be forced by law to face their
OL,8,Fvictims and families in Channel Island
OL,9,Fcourts.
OL,11,FCurrently, there is no legal
OL,12,Fobligation for convicted criminals to
OL,13,Fturn up for their sentencing across
OL,14,Fthe Bailiwicks.
OL,16,FHowever, the question has been asked
OL,17,Fif this should change after a
OL,18,Fconvicted rapist refused to turn up to
OL,19,Fhear his sentence in Jersey's Royal
OL,20,FCourt on Thursday 8 December 2025.
