OL,3,CShould the Channel Islands compel
OL,4,Ccriminals to face victims in court?
OL,6,FThe man who murdered Olivia refused to
OL,7,Fleave his cell for sentencing or hear
OL,8,Fthe impact her death caused her family
OL,9,Fthrough their impact statements.
OL,11,FCheryl Korbel, Olivia's mother, has
OL,12,Ftravelled from Liverpool to London to
OL,13,Fcampaign for a law to force criminals
OL,14,Fto face their victims in court.
OL,16,FShe told ITV News that it made her
OL,17,F"frustrated and angry" for her
OL,18,Fdaughter's killer not to be present in
OL,19,Fcourt.
