OL,3,CShould the Channel Islands compel
OL,4,Ccriminals to face victims in court?
OL,6,FThat can happen even if it's against
OL,7,Ftheir will under a court order, but
OL,8,Fnothing has actually been enshrined in
OL,9,Flaw to get defendants into the dock.
OL,11,FFor survivors of any crime, having the
OL,12,Fchoice to face their perpetrator is
OL,13,Fseen as vital by campaigners.
OL,15,FIt'll be interesting to see if that
OL,16,Fcould change.
